yuna: This morning I opened my notebook to the first page I wrote in this city.
yuna: "Objective\: prove competence. Return to the association."
yuna: Two lines. Clear. Measurable.
yuna: I stared at them for a long time.
yuna: Then closed the notebook without writing anything.
yuna: The alpha is at the city center today — first time it's stopped moving.
yuna: Baku knew since before dawn.
yuna: She didn't wake me immediately.
yuna: She made tea first, set it on my table, then knocked on my door.
yuna: I didn't say anything about that.
yuna: But I drank every last drop.
yuna: I keep telling myself I want to go back to the association. I've stopped being sure that's true.
[wait time="2.0"]
narrator: Sky dark since morning. Wind from every direction.
narrator: They fly into the city center — the tallest ruins, the densest vines, a place even regular spawns rarely enter.
[wait time="1.0"]
[signal arg="boss entrance"]
[wait time="5.0"]
narrator: The alpha is there.
narrator: Larger than words can describe —
narrator: — round, its hand-shaped wings spread wide, its face a set of concentric rings that feels like it's looking back.
narrator: Its movements are slow. But every movement displaces the air around it.
[wait time="2.0"]
join baku (Outlined) right
baku: (whispers)\
There it is.
